      <details class="card" style="padding: var(--space-5);">
        <summary style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: 600; font-size: var(--fs-lg);">
          What are the eligibility requirements?
        </summary>
        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3); margin-bottom: var(--space-3);">
          Applicants should be recent Ph.D. graduates (i.e., five years from the award of the
          degree) or Ph.D. students based in Europe with a general background in Security Studies
          (such as International Relations courses) but who do not yet possess specialised expertise
          in defence and security matters. Alumni of SWAMOS should not apply.
        </p>
        <p style="margin-bottom: 0;">
          Admitted applicants must complete advance reading assignments and devote their full
          attention to the workshop during its week term.
        </p>
      </details>

      <details class="card" style="padding: var(--space-5);">
        <summary style="cursor: pointer; font-weight: 600; font-size: var(--fs-lg);">
          What is the application process?
        </summary>
        <p style="margin-top: var(--space-3); margin-bottom: 0;">
          The programme admits 21 fully-funded participants every year. They receive a €1,000
          stipend to cover travel and accommodation. Applications need to be submitted by
          10 March 2023.
        </p>
      </details>

